The paper focuses on combining deep neural networks with reinforcement learning for intelligent control, specifically in the context of navigation using unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs). This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of neural networks for policy mapping and reinforcement learning for policy optimization suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the use of sensor readings and image processing for navigation suggests a possible focus on computer vision (cs.CV).
